ary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen had at least 1 daughter with John Shireford."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1316–Female":"1316–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","Abt 1316":"umbes 1316","Shireford,Warwickshire,England":"Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1316–Female":"1316–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","Abt 1316":"noin 1316","Shireford,Warwickshire,England":"Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1316–Female":"1316–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","Abt 1316":"environ 1316","Shireford,Warwickshire,England":"Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Ellen a eu au moins 1 fille avec John Shireford."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1300–Male":"1300–Verstorben","1316–Female":"1316–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1316":"1316","1300":"1300","Abt 1316":"um 1316","Shireford,Warwickshire,England":"Warwickshire, Eng